{"id":"1401.8095","submitter":"Maxim Chernodub","authors":"V. Braguta, M. N. Chernodub, V. A. Goy, K. Landsteiner, A. V.\n  Molochkov, M. I. Polikarpov","title":"Temperature dependence of the axial magnetic effect in two-color\n  quenched QCD","comments":"5 pages, 1 figure","journal-ref":"Phys. Rev. D 89, 074510 (2014)","doi":"10.1103/PhysRevD.89.074510","report-no":"IFT-UAM/CSIC-14-002","categories":"hep-lat hep-th","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  The Axial Magnetic Effect is the generation of an equilibrium dissipationless\nenergy flow of chiral fermions in the direction of the axial (chiral) magnetic\nfield. At finite temperature the dissipationless energy transfer may be\nrealized in the absence of any chemical potentials. We numerically study the\ntemperature behavior of the Axial Magnetic Effect in quenched SU(2) lattice\ngauge theory. We show that in the confinement (hadron) phase the effect is\nabsent. In the deconfinement transition region the conductivity quickly\nincreases, reaching the asymptotic $T^2$ behavior in a deep deconfinement\n(plasma) phase. Apart from an overall proportionality factor, our results\nqualitatively agree with theoretical predictions for the behavior of the energy\nflow as a function of temperature and strength of the axial magnetic field.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 31 Jan 2014 09:34:10 GMT"}],"update_date":"2014-04-23"}
